<i>noun</i>: 힌두교 <br>
<ul>
<li>
<i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>힌두교</dt><br>
<dd>a body of religious and philosophical beliefs and cultural practices native to India and based on a caste system; it is characterized by a belief in reincarnation, by a belief in a supreme being of many forms and natures, by the view that opposing theories are aspects of one eternal truth, and by a desire for liberation from earthly evils</dd><br>
<dd><i>synonyms</i>: Hinduism, Hindooism</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>
